import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(x=data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?')
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, label='Maximum Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, label='Minimum Temperature')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['wind', 'temp_max']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='wind', y='temp_max', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].astype('category')
    sns.countplot(x='weather', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
